<sect1 id="sec1">
<title>Preparation of DIG-labeled DNA probes for <emphasis role="italic">in situ</emphasis> hybridization</title>
<sect2 id="sec1-1">
<title>DIG-labeling by linear PCR</title>
<orderedlist numeration="arabic">
<listitem><para>Make the following reaction mix (total 10 &mu;l):</para>
<para>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="75">
<title/>
<tgroup cols="2">
<colspec colnum="1" colname="col1"/>
<colspec colnum="2" colname="col2"/>
<tbody>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">distilled water</entry>
<entry align="left">4.4 &mu;l</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">anchored oligo dT primers*</entry>
<entry align="left">3.0 &mu;l</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">10 &times; Taq buffer</entry>
<entry align="left">1 &mu;l</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">Taq polymerase</entry>
<entry align="left">0.1 &mu;l</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">10 &times; DIG-dUTP/dNTP mix**</entry>
<entry align="left">1.5 &mu;l</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left"><para>cDNA insert (> 3.5 ng/ &mu;l)</para><para>amplified from yk clone using T7/T3 primers</para></entry>
<entry align="left">0.6 &mu;l</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left"><para>* anchored oligo dT primers:</para>
<para>5.3 &mu;M (dT)<subscript>17</subscript>dG/5.3 &mu;M (dT)<subscript>17</subscript>dC/21.3 &mu;M (dT)<subscript>17</subscript>dA (This is to avoid the effect of poly-A stretch. Other vector primers may be used.)</para>
<para>** 10 &times; DIG-dUTP/dNTP mix:</para>
<para>0.35 mM DIG-dUTP/0.65 mM dTTP/1mM each d(A, G, C)TP</para></entry>
<entry/>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table></para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Subject to thermal cycling:</para>
<para>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>hot start at 95 &deg;C for 45 sec</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>95 &deg;C &times; 15 sec</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>45 &deg;C &times; 1 min</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>72 &deg;C &times; 1 min</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>50 cycles</para></listitem></itemizedlist></para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Add 10 &mu;l of 10 mM EDTA</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Pass through G-50 spin colum chromatography (ca. 250 &mu;l bed volume)</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Add 5 &mu;l of TSE</para></listitem></orderedlist>
</sect2>
<sect2 id="sec1-2">
<title>Chopping the probes by DNaseI digestion</title>
<orderedlist numeration="arabic" continuation="restarts">
<listitem><para>Make the following reaction mix (total 25 &mu;l) on ice:</para>
<para>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="75">
<title/>
<tgroup cols="2">
<colspec colnum="1" colname="col1"/>
<colspec colnum="2" colname="col2"/>
<tbody>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">The G-50 elutate</entry>
<entry align="left">20 &mu;l</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">10 mg/ml Salmon sperm DNA</entry>
<entry align="left">1 &mu;l</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">distilled water</entry>
<entry align="left">0.5 &mu;l</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">10 &times; DNase buffer*</entry>
<entry align="left">2.5 &mu;l</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">DNaseI (16 &mu;g/ml)**</entry>
<entry align="left">1 &mu;l</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left"><para>* 10 &times; DNase buffer: 0.5 M TrisHCl pH 7.5, 0.1 M MgCl<subscript>2</subscript></para>
<para>** Dilute stock solution (1 mg/ml) with 0.1 M NaCl.</para>
<para>(Note : Best size of probes is about 100 bases. Longer probes may cause high background. The concentrations of the enzyme should be optimized by pilot experiments.)</para></entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table></para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Incubate at 37 &deg;C for 30 min</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Transfer on ice</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Add 5 &mu;l of 0.1 M EDTA</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Heat at 75 &deg;C for 5 min</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Check the size by alkaline agarose gel electrophoresis and DIG detection, if necessary</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Store frozen</para></listitem></orderedlist>
</sect2>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="sec2">
<title>Fixation of embryos from a small number of worms</title>
<orderedlist numeration="arabic">
<listitem><para>Take siliconized 1.5 ml eppendorf tubes</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Place about 100 &mu;l of distilled water on the (inside) top of the lids</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Pick and transfer 40-50 gravid worms into the water. If you need very late stage embryos:</para>
<orderedlist numeration="loweralpha">
<listitem><para>Add 50 &mu;l of suspension of <emphasis role="italic">E. coli</emphasis> <ulink url="http://www.wormbase.org/db/get?name=OP50;class=Strain" role="_blank">OP50</ulink> in S-basal</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Cover the lid with the body of the tube</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Let stand at 20 &deg;C overnight</para></listitem></orderedlist></listitem>
<listitem><para>Spin down the worms.</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Add equal volume of 2 &times; alkaline-bleach solution and mix well</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Leave at r.t. for 10 min to dissolve the adult bodies</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Add 1 ml of <ulink url="http://www.wormbase.org/db/get?name=M9;class=Clone" role="_blank"><ulink url="http://www.wormbase.org/db/get?name=M9;class=Strain" role="_blank">M9</ulink></ulink> buffer at 4 &deg;C</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Centrifuge at 2500 rpm for 30 sec at 4 &deg;C in a swing rotor</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Remove the sup carefully, leaving about 100 &mu;l of the sup to avoid removing the embryos</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Repeat steps 7-9 three more times</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Add an equal volume of 3 mg/ml chitinase</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Mix and incubate at r.t. for 3 min</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Spin at 2500 rpm for 30 sec at 4 &deg;C</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Reduce the volume to about 50 &mu;l</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Transfer the embryos to a poly-L-lysine coated 3-well slide using a siliconized pipette tip</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Add a half volume of 4% gelatin, 2% BSA, and mix gently by pipeting</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Let stand for several minutes to allow the embryos settled down to the bottom</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Cover with a cover slip (24 &times; 40 mm)</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Place it on the top of a dry ice block</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Freeze for 7 min at -70 &deg;C</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Peel off the cover slip quickly</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Soak the slide in methanol cooled at -20 &deg;C for 5 min</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Rehydrate by soaking the slide in the series of the following solutions pre-cooled at 4 &deg;C:</para>
<para>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="75">
<title/>
<tgroup cols="2">
<colspec colnum="1" colname="col1"/>
<colspec colnum="2" colname="col2"/>
<tbody>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">methanol</entry>
<entry align="left">for 5 min</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">methanol:formaldehyde-Hepes-PBS* = 35:15</entry>
<entry align="left">for 2 min</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">methanol:formaldehyde-Hepes-PBS* = 25:25</entry>
<entry align="left">for 2 min</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">methanol:formaldehyde-Hepes-PBS* = 15:35</entry>
<entry align="left">for 2 min</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">formaldehyde-Hepes-PBS*</entry>
<entry align="left">for 20 min</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</para>
<para>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="75">
<title/>
<tgroup cols="2">
<colspec colnum="1" colname="col1"/>
<colspec colnum="2" colname="col2"/>
<tbody>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">*formaldehyde-Hepes-PBS</entry>
<entry/>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">Hepes</entry>
<entry align="left">200ml</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">10xPBS</entry>
<entry align="left">25ml</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">formaldehyde</entry>
<entry align="left">25ml</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Dehydrate by soaking the slide in the series of the following solutions at r.t.:</para>
<para>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="75">
<title/>
<tgroup cols="2">
<colspec colnum="1" colname="col1"/>
<colspec colnum="2" colname="col2"/>
<tbody>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">ethanol:PBS=15:35</entry>
<entry align="left">for 5min</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">ethanol:PBS=25:25</entry>
<entry align="left">for 5min</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">ethanol:PBS=35:15</entry>
<entry align="left">for 5 min</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">ethanol</entry>
<entry align="left">for 5 min &times; 2 times</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table></para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Store in ethanol at &minus;20 &deg;C.</para></listitem></orderedlist>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="sec3">
<title>Large scale fixation of embryos</title>
<sect2 id="sec3-1">
<title>Harvesting of embryos</title>
<orderedlist numeration="arabic">
<listitem><para>Get a plenty of worms from a mixed stage population</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Wash the worms 2 times with <ulink url="http://www.wormbase.org/db/get?name=M9;class=Clone" role="_blank"><ulink url="http://www.wormbase.org/db/get?name=M9;class=Strain" role="_blank">M9</ulink></ulink> buffer</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Collect L1-L3 by sieving through 50 &mu;m Nylon mesh</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Allow the collected worms to grow to young adults in liquid culture</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Take 1 ml packed worms from the culture, which will give 8-15 slides for <emphasis role="italic">in situ</emphasis></para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Resuspend the worms in 4 ml water in a 15 ml Falcon tube (clear type)</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Add 5 ml of 2 &times; alkali-bleach solution, mix well and let stand for 10 min</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Force the worms out through a 23-gauge needle onto nylon mesh</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Collect embryos by spinning the filtrate at 800 &times; g using a swing rotor</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Wash the embryos 4 times with <ulink url="http://www.wormbase.org/db/get?name=M9;class=Clone" role="_blank"><ulink url="http://www.wormbase.org/db/get?name=M9;class=Strain" role="_blank">M9</ulink></ulink> and transferred into a siliconized eppendorf tube</para></listitem></orderedlist>
</sect2>
<sect2 id="sec3-2">
<title>Fixation</title>
<orderedlist numeration="arabic">
<listitem><para>Take 100 &mu;l (packed volume) of the embryos and adjust the volume to 200 &mu;l with <ulink url="http://www.wormbase.org/db/get?name=M9;class=Clone" role="_blank"><ulink url="http://www.wormbase.org/db/get?name=M9;class=Strain" role="_blank">M9</ulink></ulink></para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Add 200 &mu;l of yatalase (15 mg/ml in 0.3 M mannitol) and vigourously shake for 75 sec</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Wash the embryos 3 times with EH buffer (Embryo Handling buffer)</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Wash the embryos with Basal EH buffer</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Resuspend the embryos in 1 ml of Basal EH buffer. (Note: For success, it is desired that 20-30% of embryos are devitellinized at this step)</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Place 30 &mu;l/well of Basal EH buffer onto each well of poly-L-lysine coated 8-well slides</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Dispense 5 &mu;l/well of the embryo suspension into the buffer at each well</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Let stand for 10 min at 4 &deg;C to settle the embryos to the bottom</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Remove the buffer, and immediately immerse in methanol at -20 &deg;C for 5 min</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Rehydrate the embryos by immersing the slides in the follwoing series at 4 &deg;C. The solutions must be pre-cooled at 4 &deg;C.</para>
<para>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="75">
<title/>
<tgroup cols="2">
<colspec colnum="1" colname="col1"/>
<colspec colnum="2" colname="col2"/>
<tbody>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">methanol</entry>
<entry align="left">5 min</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">methanol:3.7% formaldehyde in hepes-PBS = 7:3</entry>
<entry align="left">2 min</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">methanol:3.7% formaldehyde in hepes-PBS = 1:1</entry>
<entry align="left">2 min</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">methanol:3.7% formaldehyde in hepes-PBS = 3:7</entry>
<entry align="left">2 min</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">3.7% formaldehyde in hepes-PBS</entry>
<entry align="left">75 min at 22 &deg;C</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table></para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Dehydrate the embryos by immersing the slides in the following series at r.t.</para>
<para>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="75">
<title/>
<tgroup cols="2">
<colspec colnum="1" colname="col1"/>
<colspec colnum="2" colname="col2"/>
<tbody>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">ethanol:PBS = 3:7</entry>
<entry align="left">5 min</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">ethanol:PBS = 1:1</entry>
<entry align="left">5 min</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">ethanol:PBS = 7:3</entry>
<entry align="left">5 min</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">ethanol</entry>
<entry align="left">5 min &times; 2 times</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table></para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Store in ethanol at -20 &deg;C.</para></listitem></orderedlist>
</sect2>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="sec4">
<title>Hybridization and signal detection</title>
<sect2 id="sec4-1">
<title>Proteinase K treatment</title>
<orderedlist numeration="arabic">
<listitem><para>Rehydrate the embryos by immersing the follwoing ethanol series:</para>
<para>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="75">
<title/>
<tgroup cols="2">
<colspec colnum="1" colname="col1"/>
<colspec colnum="2" colname="col2"/>
<tbody>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">0.03% H2O2 in ethanol:PBS = 7:3</entry>
<entry align="left">2 min</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">ethanol:PBS = 1:1</entry>
<entry align="left">5 min</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">ethanol:PBS = 3:7</entry>
<entry align="left">5 min</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table></para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Wash the slides once by immersing in PBT for 5 min. *For late stage embryos, additional HCl treatment is effective, which can cut glycosid bonds of the proteoglycan that appear on late stage embryos.</para>
<orderedlist inheritnum="ignore">
<listitem><para>a) Immerse the slides in 0.2 N HCl for 20 min at r.t.</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>b) Wash the slides 2 times in PBT for 5 min</para></listitem></orderedlist></listitem>
<listitem><para>Immerse the slides in proteinase K (10 &mu;g/ml in PBT) and incubate at r.t. for 11 min</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Stop the digestion by immersing the slides in 2 mg/ml glycine in PBT for 2 min</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Wash the slides twice by immersing them in PBT for 2 min each</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Refix by immersing the slides in 3.7% formaldehyde in hepes-PBS at r.t. for 50 min</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Wash the slides twice in PBT for 5 min each</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Immerse the slides in 2 mg/ml glycine in PBT at r.t. for 5 min</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Wash the slides in PBT for 5 min</para></listitem>
</orderedlist>
</sect2>
<sect2 id="sec4-2">
<title>Pre-Hybridization</title>
<orderedlist numeration="arabic">
<listitem><para>Immerse the slides in the following series of mixtures;</para>
<para>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="75">
<title/>
<tgroup cols="2">
<colspec colnum="1" colname="col1"/>
<colspec colnum="2" colname="col2"/>
<tbody>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">50% formamide, 5 &times; SSC, heparin, 0.1% Tween:PBT = 1:1</entry>
<entry align="left">10 min</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">50% formamide, 5 &times; SSC, heparin, 0.1% Tween</entry>
<entry align="left">10 min</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table></para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Wipe off the slides</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Draw a rectangle surrounding the sample wells using a IMMUNO pen to make a ridge</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Add 250 &mu;l of heat denatured (at 99 &deg;C for 10 min and quickly chilled for 5 min) hybridization solution for each 8-well slide</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Place the slide in a moist chamber containing a paper towel wetted with 50% formamide, 5 &times; SSC. (No need to use coverslips)</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Incubate at 48 &deg;C for 1 hr</para></listitem></orderedlist>
</sect2>
<sect2 id="sec4-3">
<title>Hybridization</title>
<orderedlist numeration="arabic">
<listitem><para>Add 50 &mu;l of heat-denatured DNA probes for each slide. (The final concentrations of probes is about 0.06 &mu;g/ml)</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Cover the slide with a parafilm coverslip to reduce evaporation</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Incubate the slides at 48 &deg;C overnight in the moist chamber</para></listitem></orderedlist>
</sect2>
<sect2 id="sec4-4">
<title>Washing</title>
<orderedlist numeration="arabic">
<listitem><para>Wash the slides in the following series of washing solutins at 48 &deg;C with slight agitation</para>
<para>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="75">
<title/>
<tgroup cols="2">
<colspec colnum="1" colname="col1"/>
<colspec colnum="2" colname="col2"/>
<tbody>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">50% formamide, 5 &times; SSC, heparin, 0.1% Tween:PBT = 1:1 (First washing is performed in separate containers for every 2 min slides)</entry>
<entry/>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">50% formamide, 5 &times; SSC, heparin, 0.1% Tween:PBT = 1:1</entry>
<entry align="left">10 min &times; 2 times</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">0.8 &times; PBS, 0.1% CHAPS</entry>
<entry align="left">20 min &times; 4 times</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table></para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Wash the slides twice in PBT for 5 min at r.t. to remove CHAPS.</para></listitem></orderedlist>
</sect2>
<sect2 id="sec4-5">
<title>Probe detection</title>
<orderedlist numeration="arabic">
<listitem><para>Incubate the slides in PBtr (PBS, 0.1% Triton-X100, 0.1% BSA, 0.01% NaN<subscript>3</subscript>) for 1.5 hr at r.t.</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Cover the embryos with 250 &mu;l of anti-DIG conjugate (dilute 1:2500)/8-well slide</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Incubate for 2 hrs at r.t. in a moist chamber. (no need to use coverslips)</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Wash the slides with PBtr 4 times with slight agitation</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Wash the slides with the staining buffer (see reagents) twice for 5 min each at r.t.</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Color development</para>
<orderedlist inheritnum="ignore">
<listitem><para>a) Mix 180 &mu;l of NBT and 140 &mu;l of BCIP in 40 ml of staining buffer.</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>b) Immerse the slides in the mixture for 1 hr at 22 &deg;C in the dark, monitoring the extent of the staining.</para></listitem></orderedlist></listitem>
<listitem><para>Wash the slides three times with PBS, 20 mM EDTA to stop the reaction.</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>If necessary, incubate the slides in 1 &mu;g/ml DAPI in Tris buffer at 4 &deg;C for 30 min.</para></listitem></orderedlist>
</sect2>
<sect2 id="sec4-6">
<title>Mounting</title>
<sect3 id="sec4-6-1">
<title>Permanent mount 1</title>
<orderedlist numeration="arabic">
<listitem><para>Add about 90 &mu;l of &ldquo;MOUNT-QUICK AQUEOUS&rdquo; onto the embryos on the slide</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Cover with a coverslip</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Let stand one day to dry up</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Seal up the edge of the coverslip using nail varnish</para></listitem></orderedlist>
</sect3>
<sect3 id="sec4-6-2">
<title>Permanent mount 2</title>
<orderedlist numeration="arabic">
<listitem><para>Dehydrate with the following ethanol series:</para>
<para>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="75">
<title/>
<tgroup cols="2">
<colspec colnum="1" colname="col1"/>
<colspec colnum="2" colname="col2"/>
<tbody>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">ethanol:PBS = 3:7</entry>
<entry align="left">5 min</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">ethanol:PBS = 1:1</entry>
<entry align="left">5 min</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">ethanol:PBS = 7:3</entry>
<entry align="left">5 min</entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">ethanol</entry>
<entry align="left">5 min &times; 2 times</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table></para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Wash once with ethanol:Histo-Clear (National Diagnostics) = 1:1</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Wash once with Histo-Clear</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Add drops of Mount-Quick onto the embryos and cover with a coverslip</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Leave the slide at 40 &deg;C for several hours</para></listitem></orderedlist>
<para>(Note : Hybridization signals by this method tend to be weaker than those by other methods and to diffuse, but preservation of morphology is better than other methods)</para>
</sect3>
<sect3 id="sec4-6-3">
<title>Glycerol mount</title>
<orderedlist numeration="arabic">
<listitem><para>Add drops of 90% glycerol, 10 mM Tris, 1% n-propylgallate onto the embryos</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Cover with a coverslip which are dotted with vaselin:solid paraffin = 9:1 at the 4 corners as spacer</para></listitem></orderedlist>
</sect3>
</sect2>
</sect1>
